Preheat your #oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{3} into 2cm thick wedges (peeling optional).

Pop onto a large (lined) #baking tray.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @shallot{1} into small pieces.

Cut the @tomato{2} into 2cm chunks.

In a #bowl, mix the shallot and tomato with the @apple cider vinegar{1%sachet} and @sugar{1%tsp} (double for 4p).

Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Set aside, continuing to stir every so often.

Halve the @cabbage{1}, cut out and discard the tough core, then thinly slice.

In a separate #bowl, mix the cabbage with the @sweet Asian sauce{2%sachets}.

Season to taste with salt and pepper and set aside.

Cut @Irish chicken breast{320%grams} into 1cm slices.

IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken.

Place a #pan over medium heat with a drizzle of oil.

Add the chicken. Season with salt and pepper.

Fry until cooked through, ~{3-6%minutes} each side. Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Remove from the pan. Cover to keep warm.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging used to keep it fresh.

Stir the @coconut milk{1%pack} (or shake the packet) to dissolve any lumps.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with coconut milk, @peanut butter{1%sachet}, @rogan josh curry paste{1%sachet}, @ketjap manis{1%sachet} and @sugar{1%tsp} (double for 4p).

Mix to combine and bring to the boil. Lower the heat and cook until thickened and creamy, stirring continuously, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Remove from the heat and season to taste with salt and pepper.

Pop the @tortilla{8} into the oven to warm, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Top your tortillas with Asian slaw and fried chicken.

Drizzle over the sauce from the pan and spoon over the tomato salsa.

Serve any remaining sauce on the side for dipping.

Plate the potato wedges alongside.